narratives.question_text: How would you summarize ECON 110 05 for a fellow student? Would you recommend ECON 110 05 to another student? Why or why not?
comments: Take it if you're interested in methodology of research and etc/
Definitely - reading material is interesting but I heard she's not coming back next year, that would definitely put a damper on the class for me.
Be aware of the fact that there's quite a few psych-heavy readings (psychology is in the title of the course after all). Besides that, I really enjoyed the class. Loved the professor.
If there's another class called "Democracy and Psychology of Inequality," I highly recommend that you take it if the material interests you.
If you're interested in the subject matter in the slightest, I would recommend it.
